cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to predict financial asset prices using news articles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and multiple kernel learning, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with financial data, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Economics).
